The paper discusses the wireless backhaul traffic in future cellular networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure and protocols. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the energy efficiency of wireless backhaul networks, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of millimeter wave communication technologies could also place the paper under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the comparison of different network architectures and frequency bands, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.COMM (Communications and Networking). Finally, the paper could also be categorized under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as it discusses the challenges and research advances in deploying future 5G wireless backhaul networks.
